{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-timeline-js","path":"/siboehm/awesome-learn-datascience/week/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"awesomeList":{"repo":"siboehm/awesome-learn-datascience","descriptionHTML":"<div>\n<g-emoji class=\"g-emoji\" alias=\"chart_with_upwards_trend\" fallback-src=\"https://github.githubassets.com/images/icons/emoji/unicode/1f4c8.png\">📈</g-emoji> Curated list of resources to help you get started with Data Science</div>","description":":chart_with_upwards_trend: Curated list of resources to help you get started with Data Science","stargazerCount":518,"repoUpdatedTime":1603985148000},"awesomeListMeta":{"readmeParsedAt":"2021-06-30T23:19:35.548Z"},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>Various other helpful tools and resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://spacy.io/\">Spacy</a> - Open source toolkit for working with text-based data.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-07-22T16:13:37.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is Data Science?</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2voPJUi\">Data Science for Business (Book)</a> - An introduction to Data Science and its use as a business asset.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-05-13T08:55:33.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>General</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://amzn.to/2GSjjrK\">O'Reilly Data Science from Scratch (Book)</a> - Data processing, implementation, and visualization with example code.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-04-30T07:28:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>General</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.coursera.org/specializations/data-science-python\">Coursera Applied Data Science</a> - Online Course using Python that covers most of the relevant toolkits.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-04-30T07:28:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is Data Science?</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.quora.com/What-is-the-difference-between-Data-Analytics-Data-Analysis-Data-Mining-Data-Science-Machine-Learning-and-Big-Data-1?share=1\">Explanation of important vocabulary</a> - Differentiation of Big Data, Machine Learning, Data Science.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Common Algorithms and Procedures</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1832076/what-is-the-difference-between-supervised-learning-and-unsupervised-learning\">Supervised vs unsupervised learning</a> - The two most common types of Machine Learning algorithms.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Common Algorithms and Procedures</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://nbviewer.jupyter.org/github/jakevdp/PythonDataScienceHandbook/blob/master/notebooks/05.03-Hyperparameters-and-Model-Validation.ipynb\">Cross validation</a> - Evaluate the performance of your algorithm / model.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Common Algorithms and Procedures</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://nbviewer.jupyter.org/github/jakevdp/PythonDataScienceHandbook/blob/master/notebooks/05.04-Feature-Engineering.ipynb\">Feature engineering</a> - Modifying the data to better model predictions.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Common Algorithms and Procedures</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.analyticsvidhya.com/blog/2017/02/introduction-to-ensembling-along-with-implementation-in-r/\">Model ensemble: Explanation</a> - Combine multiple models into one for better performance.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>Learning Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oVp1vrfL_w4&#x26;list=PLQVvvaa0QuDe8XSftW-RAxdo6OmaeL85M\">YouTube tutorial series by sentdex</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>pandas</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.datacamp.com/courses/pandas-foundations\">DataCamp pandas foundations</a> - Paid course, but 30 free days upon account creation (enough to complete course).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>pandas</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/pandas-dev/pandas/blob/master/doc/cheatsheet/Pandas_Cheat_Sheet.pdf\">Pandas cheatsheet</a> - Quick overview over the most important functions.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>Jupyter Notebook</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://elitedatascience.com/python-seaborn-tutorial\">Seaborn data visualization tutorial</a> - Plot library that works great with Jupyter.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>Various other helpful tools and resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.continuum.io/downloads\">Anaconda Python distribution</a> - Contains most of the important Python packages for Data Science.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>Various other helpful tools and resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Microsoft/LightGBM\">LightGBM gradient boosting framework</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Microsoft/LightGBM\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">12.5k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":12497,\"repo\":\"Microsoft/LightGBM\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Successfully used in many Kaggle challenges.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>Various other helpful tools and resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/\">Amazon AWS</a> - Rent cloud servers for more timeconsuming calculations (r4.xlarge server is a good place to start).</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science Challenges for Beginners</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.dataquest.io/blog/kaggle-getting-started/\">Walkthrough: House prices challenge</a> - Walkthrough through a simple challenge on house prices.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science Challenges for Beginners</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.drivendata.org/competitions/2/warm-up-predict-blood-donations/\">Blood Donation Challenge</a> - Predict if a donor will donate again.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science Challenges for Beginners</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/c/titanic\">Titanic Challenge</a> - Predict survival on the Titanic.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science Challenges for Beginners</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.drivendata.org/competitions/7/pump-it-up-data-mining-the-water-table/\">Water Pump Challenge</a> - Predict the operating condition of water pumps in Africa.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-09-25T22:02:18.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>What is Data Science?</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.quora.com/What-is-data-science\">'What is Data Science?' on Quora</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-08-06T20:13:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Common Algorithms and Procedures</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.cs.umd.edu/%7Esamir/498/10Algorithms-08.pdf\">Scientific introduction to 10 important Data Science algorithms</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-08-06T20:13:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>scikit-learn</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://scikit-learn.org/stable/user_guide.html\">Scikit-learn complete user guide</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-08-06T20:13:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>scikit-learn</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://machinelearningmastery.com/ensemble-machine-learning-algorithms-python-scikit-learn/\">Model ensemble: Implementation in Python</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-08-06T20:13:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>numpy</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.datacamp.com/community/tutorials/python-numpy-tutorial#gs.h3DvLnk\">Numpy tutorial on DataCamp</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-15T11:18:46.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Common Algorithms and Procedures</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://nbviewer.jupyter.org/github/jakevdp/PythonDataScienceHandbook/blob/master/notebooks/05.05-Naive-Bayes.ipynb\">9 important Data Science algorithms and their implementation</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-12T13:57:46.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>Learning Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.learnpython.org/\">Interactive Python tutorial website</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-12T13:57:46.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>pandas</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.synesthesiam.com/posts/an-introduction-to-pandas.html\">Introduction to pandas</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-12T13:57:46.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>scikit-learn</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://nbviewer.jupyter.org/github/jakevdp/PythonDataScienceHandbook/blob/master/notebooks/05.02-Introducing-Scikit-Learn.ipynb\">Introduction and first model application</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-12T13:57:46.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>scikit-learn</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://scikit-learn.org/stable/tutorial/machine_learning_map/\">Rough guide for choosing estimators</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-12T13:57:46.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>Jupyter Notebook</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://jupyter.org/install.html\">Downloading and running first Jupyter notebook</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-12T13:57:46.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>Jupyter Notebook</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/sudalairajkumar/simple-exploration-notebook-instacart\">Example notebook for data exploration</a></li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-12T13:57:46.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Science using Python</h2><h3>Various other helpful tools and resources</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/drivendata/cookiecutter-data-science\">Template folder structure for organizing Data Science projects</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/drivendata/cookiecutter-data-science\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">4.6k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":4577,\"repo\":\"drivendata/cookiecutter-data-science\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--></li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-12T13:57:46.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>More advanced resources and lists</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/bulutyazilim/awesome-datascience\">Awesome Data Science</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/bulutyazilim/awesome-datascience\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relat